<div class="font-size-20 bold text-center margin-bottom-20">Questions & Answers</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="steps">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> What are the different steps to set my shop?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-steps" style="display: none;">
    <ul>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10 font-size-15"><strong>Step 1:</strong> In “Creation zone”:</li>
        <p>Upload your pictures <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Set your commission <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Click “Next”</p>
        <p>Place picture on products <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Click on picture you want to use <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Click on “product selection” button <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Select product <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Place picture on product <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Click on “add to my shop” button 
            Your creations summary <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> If wanted, rename your product <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Tick the “publish” box</p>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10 font-size-15"><strong>Step 2:</strong> In “Your shop”:</li>
        <p>Edit your shop information <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Fill-in shop title/motto/website/shop description field <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Upload your shop logo & header picture <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Add your Social media links <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Save</p>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10 font-size-15"><strong>Step 3:</strong> In “User account”:</li>
        <p>Fill-in all fields of “personal information” <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Fill-in your Paypal account details <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> Set a payment release level amount.</p>
        <hr>
        <p>You are all set.</p>
        <p>Visit your shop there: “My shop” <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span> “Visit my shop”</p>
        <p>And start to promote it.</p>
    </ul>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="giftattitude-role">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> What does Gift attitude website handles?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-giftattitude-role" style="display: none;">
    <p><strong>We handle:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10">Order process</li>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10">Online payment</li>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10">Product Storage</li>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10">Product personalization</li>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10">Order Shipping</li>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10">Customer service</li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="shop-owner-role">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> What do I have to handle?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-shop-owner-role" style="display: none;">
    <p><strong>You handle:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10">Product creation</li>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10">Your shop looking</li>
        <li class="margin-bottom-10">Your shop promotion</li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="pay">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> Do I have to pay anything?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-pay" style="display: none;">
    <p>No, creating your own shop with Gift Attitude is completely free and will forever be. No credit card registration is required as far as you will never have anything to pay to us.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="price"><span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> What is the “sale price” composed of?</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-price" style="display: none;">
    <p class="bold">Sale price = Product price (our benefit) + Commission set (your benefit)</p>
    <p class="underline">Let’s say:</p>
    <div class="padding-left-20">
        <p>Our product price is <strong>$3.25/pc</strong></p>
        <p>Commission you set for your picture/design is <strong>$2.40/pc</strong></p>
        <p>That product will be sold on your website <strong>$5.65/pc</strong></p>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="discount">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> There are some progressive discounts for quantities over 5pcs. Who bears this discount?  And how is this discount calculated?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-discount" style="display: none;">
    <p class="bold">Discount provided is exclusively beared by Gift Attitude and is calculated as follow:</p>
    <div class="padding-left-20">
        <li>From 5pcs: <strong>10% off</strong> on “Product price”</li>
        <li>From 10pcs: <strong>20% off</strong> on “Product price”</li>
        <li>From 25pcs: <strong>50% off</strong> on “Product price”</li>
        <li>From 50pcs: <strong>70% off</strong> on “Product price”</li>
        <li>From 100pcs: <strong>80% off</strong> on “Product price”</li>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="conditions">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> What are the conditions to get paid?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-conditions" style="display: none;">
    <p class="bold">To get paid, several conditions need to be completed. You need to have:</p>
    <div class="padding-left-20">
        <li>Reach your payment release level ($20 minimum)</li>
        <li>Filled-in all your personal information</li>
        <li>Keyed-in and validate your paypal account information details</li>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="when-paid">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> When are my commission paid?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-when-paid" style="display: none;">
    <p>Gift Attitude pays cumulated commission amount on the 1st of each month (if working day) as far as Payment release level is reached.</p>
    <p>In other words, if I set $100 as my commission release level, and that on 31.03 I only accumulated $92.5, then payment won’t be release, but will be saved for the next month. If on 31.04, I accumulated $103 (including amount accumulated in February), then the full amount will be released.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="how-get-paid">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> How are my commissions paid?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-how-get-paid" style="display: none;">
    <p><strong>All commissions are paid through Paypal.</strong></p>
    <p>If you don’t have an existing paypal account, creating one is fast & free and withdrawing the money is easy.</p>
    <p>You can create an account here: <a class="btn btn-primary btn-sm" target="_blank" href="https://www.paypal.com/webapps/mpp/account-selection" title="Create a paypal account" >Create a paypal account</a></p>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="max-commission">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> What is the maximum amount of commissions I can set? 
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-max-commission" style="display: none;">
    <p>There is <strong>no maximum amount for your commissions</strong>. Nevertheless, Gift Attitude advises not to set commissions over <strong>$2 per picture/design</strong>, to keep sale prices attractive</p>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="creations">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> How many creations can I post?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-creations" style="display: none;">
    <p>You can post <strong>as many creations as you want</strong>. The same products can be posted several times with different picture/design on it. And the same design can be posted several times on different products.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="limitation">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> Is there any limitation in term of design/picture?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-limitation" style="display: none;">
    <p>We don’t have any limitation in term of design. For copyrighted designs, owner must be able to bring the proof that he owns the copyright, in case complaints are received. If sales featuring controversial design have occurred, and if it is proved that the shop owner doesn’t own the copyright, the shop owner will be asked to pay back commission paid by Gift Attitude on concerned orders.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="follow-up-activity">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> How can I follow up activity on my shop?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-follow-up-activity" style="display: none;">
    <p>All orders received on your shop are recorded on your <a href="{$base_uri}{$custom_shop_name}/admin/dashboard" title="Dashboard">“dashboard”</a>. For each order, Gift attitude will update regularly order status and package tracking number to keep you informed. It might take up to 48h for a new order to show up on your dashboard.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block-title font-size-15" data-id-dropdown-block="data-security">
    <span class="chevron glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span> Are my data secured?
</div>
<div class="col-xs-12 dropdown-block dropdown-block-data-security" style="display: none;">
    <p>Your account keys and your personal data are secured on our server. Moreover, we commit not to give or sell your data to any third party company under any circumstances.</p>
</div>
